   plain:'Cervical os: the opening, normally 1-3mm. Dilates to 10cm during childbirth. Cervical mucus: changes from thick/hostile to thin/fertile around ovulation. Cervical crypts: store viable sperm up to 5 days. Pap smear: screens for precancerous changes in cervical cells.',
